**Implementing a Masked Input Field for Social Security Numbers**
=============================================================

A masked input field can be implemented using JavaScript and HTML to format a social security number during user input. Here's an example of how to implement a masked input field for social security numbers:

**HTML:**

```html
<!-- HTML Form Structure -->
<form id="social-security-form">
  <h2>Enter Social Security Number</h2>
  <label for="social-security-number">Social Security Number:</label>
  <input type="text" id="social-security-number" name="social-security-number" required>
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
  <div id="error-message"></div>
</form>
```

**JavaScript:**

```javascript
// Get the input element
const socialSecurityNumberInput = document.getElementById('social-security-number');

// Add event listener to the input element's keyup event
socialSecurityNumberInput.addEventListener('keyup', () => {
  // Format the social security number as XXX-XX-XXXX
  const formattedNumber = formatSocialSecurityNumber(socialSecurityNumberInput.value);
  socialSecurityNumberInput.value = formattedNumber;
});

// Function to format the social security number
function formatSocialSecurityNumber(number) {
  // Use a regular expression to match the social security number format
  const pattern = /^\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}$/;
  if (pattern.test(number)) {
    // Return the formatted social security number
    return number;
  } else {
    // Return the unformatted social security number
    return number.replace(/\D+/g, '');
  }
}
```

